techmeme.title: Sonos names interim CEO Tom Conrad as CEO, effective immediately, as it works to restore confidence after its app disaster; Conrad took the job in January 2025 (Chris Welch/Bloomberg)
Eye Security: hackers have breached ~400 government agencies, corporations, and other groups via the SharePoint breach, up from an estimated 60 on July 22 (Ryan Gallagher/Bloomberg)
The UK partners with Deliveroo, Just Eat, and Uber Eats to curb illegal food delivery work, share more data, and combat a secondary market in rider accounts (Financial Times)
Compliance tech startup Vanta raised a $150M Series D led by Wellington Management at a $4.15B valuation, up from $2.45B after raising $150M in July 2024 (Paayal Zaveri/Bloomberg)
Apple launches AppleCare One, an insurance plan covering up to three devices for $20 per month, including battery replacements, accidental damage, and more (Samantha Kelly/Bloomberg)
